Using the code below, update the function to find the average of three positive integers, where each integer is within the range of 1 to 100 (inclusive). If any of the numbers are negative or greater than 100, raise a ValueError exception with the message "Invalid input, all numbers must be positive integers within the range of 1 to 100.". Additionally, if any of the numbers are not divisible by 5, round the average to the nearest whole number using the rounding mode of your choice. 

def find_average(num1, num2, num3):
  if num1 < 1 or num1 > 100 or num2 < 1 or num2 > 100 or num3 < 1 or num3 > 100:
    raise ValueError("Invalid input, all numbers must be positive integers within the range of 1 to 100.")

